Package foldocpos

Implements the ontology parser using NLP and part-of-speech information for FOLDOC-style dictionaries

          Description

Class Summary
DebugDictAdapter A DictAdapter that provides debugging output of tokens to stdout
DictAdapter An interface for dictionary-style callbacks, with empty implementations
DictHandler An org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler to re-interpret Dictionary-style NLP tokens for a DictAdapter.
FOLDOCReader A java Reader that re-interprets FOLDOC-style dictionaries so that the NLP parser behaves correctly.
Keywords Represents the keywords-relationship mapping.
POSParse The NLP version of the command line Parse wrapper (for POSParser)
POSParser An NLP Parser for a FOLDOC-like dictionary - creating an ontology utilising part-of-speech information
POSToker A DictAdapter that re-interpretes dictionary NLP XML tokens into parsing tokens for POSParser.
The token(...) method of a POSParser is the only callback.
ReaderTester Dumps the result of each definition to stdout, after being pre-processed by the FOLDOCReader
Stopwords Represents a set of stopwords.
